net.sf.mmm.util.collection.api

Interface TreeNode<NODE extends TreeNode<NODE>>

  • Type Parameters:
    NODE - is the generic type for self-references. Each sub-type of this interface should specialize this type to itself. End-users should use implementations where the generic is finally bound. For generic usage simply use an unbound wildcard (TreeNode<?>).
    All Superinterfaces:
    GenericTreeNode<NODE,NODE>, Node<NODE>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractTreeNode, TreeNodeSimple

    public interface TreeNode<NODE extends TreeNode<NODE>>
extends GenericTreeNode<NODE,NODE>
    This is the interface for the node a tree. The tree itself is defined by the root-node which is its only node in the tree that has no parent.
    Since:
    1.0.2
    Author:
    Joerg Hohwiller (hohwille at users.sourceforge.net)
